r 1965{{sfn|Busch|R\u00f6ll|2003|p=43}}\n\n==Translation notes==\n{{Reflist|group=\"Tr\"|30em}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=\"Note\"}}\n\n==References==\n\n===Citations===\n{{Reflist|25em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{Refbegin|30em}}\n* {{cite book\n  |last=Blair\n  |first=Clay\n  |authorlink=Clay Blair\n  |title=Hitler's U-Boat War: The Hunters, 1939\u20131942\n  |publisher=Random House\n  |year=1998\n  |isbn=978-0-30787-437-5\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last1=Busch\n  |first1=Rainer\n  |last2=R\u00f6ll\n  |first2=Hans-Joachim\n  |year=2003\n  |title=Der U-Boot-Krieg 1939\u20131945 \u2014 Die Ritterkreuztr\u00e4ger der U-Boot-Waffe von September 1939 bis Mai 1945\n  |trans-title=The U-Boat War 1939\u20131945 \u2014 The Knight's Cross Bearers of the U-Boat Force from September 1939 to May 1945\n  |language=German\n  |location=Hamburg, Berlin, Bonn Germany\n  |publisher=Verlag E.S. Mittler & Sohn\n  |isbn=978-3-8132-0515-2\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n  |last=Claasen\n  |first=Adam R. A.\n  |year=2001\n  |title=Hitler's Northern War: The Luftwaffe's Ill-Fated Campaign, 1940\u20131945\n  |location=Lawrence, KS\n  |publisher=[[University Press of Kansas]]\n  |isbn=978-0-7006-1050-1\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Edwards\n  |first=Bernard\n  |title=The Twilight of the U-boats\n  |date=2004\n  |publisher=[[Naval Institute Press]]\n  |isbn=978-1844150359\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n  |last1=Haarr\n  |first1=Geirr H.\n  |title=The Gathering Storm: The Naval War in Northern Europe September 1939 - April 1940 \n  |date=2012\n  |publisher=Seaforth Publishing\n  |isbn=978-1591148845\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n  |last=Haarr\n  |first=Geirr\n  |title=The Battle for Norway: April-June 1940\n  |publisher=Seaforth Publishing\n  |date=2010\n  |isbn=978-1-78346-905-5\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last1=Hadley \n  |first1=Michael L.\n  |authorlink=\n  |year=1995\n  |title=Count Not the Dead: The Popular Image of the German Submarine\n  |language =